Started: Tue May  5 09:18:40 IST 2026

What this does:
  - Walks the Library/ folder (auto-located)
  - For each PDF: reads page 1 text, renders cover thumbnail
  - Computes TF-IDF keywords across all PDFs
  - Detects language, year, author from filenames
  - Writes catalog.json + thumbnails/ in this folder

First run installs pymupdf and scikit-learn (~30 sec).
Then takes 15-30 minutes depending on Dropbox speed and PDF count.
Subsequent runs skip already-rendered covers, so they're fast.

